  <description type="morphology">Stems 1–4 cm. Leaves sometimes tinted pink or red proximally, small and scalelike on proximal portions of stem, enlarged distally, rosette leaves 4–7 mm; laminal cells 90–150×30–50 µm; basal cells more regularly rectangular, often somewhat narrower than distal cells; marginal cells narrower, walls thicker, forming somewhat distinct border 1–2 rows wide. Perigonia conspicuous, antheridia abundant, yellow, in disklike heads. Perichaetial leaves similar to stem leaves, smaller. Capsule 4–7 mm.</description>
