  <discussion>Roellobryon roellii is rare in Alaska, Nevada, and Utah, and is most common in areas south of the Pleistocene ice-sheets in western North America. Coastal Alaskan-northern British Columbia populations probably survived glaciation in refugia. The species has been found near sea level in coastal Alaska but generally occurs at 500–3200 m. Capsules are rare.</discussion>
